<HEADLINE>
<P>
SURVIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nicholas Daniloff makes a statement which has challenged me: " . . . The world 
saw more clearly than before that Armenians are deeply emotional and possibly 
paranoid. Like the Jews, they fear extinction" ("A Shock to the Soviet 
Foundation; In Armenian Rubble, Moscow's Ethnic Problems Grow," Editorial Page, 
Jan. 28.). 
</P>
<P>
But isn't that "normal" and shouldn't anyone become deeply emotional and on 
guard when their very existence, their identity is at stake? How else could 
Armenians and Jews have survived despite their tumultuous histories? Why not 
give credit where credit is due and salute those who survive with style? 
</P>
<P>
SHERRY TERZIAN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
