<HEADLINE>
<P>
TITANS TO MEET NO. 19 NEVADA LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton, coming off an upset of UC Santa Barbara that was the 
Titans' biggest win of the basketball season, faces a bigger challenge tonight 
as the Titans play host to 19th-ranked Nevada Las Vegas in a Big West 
Conference game tonight at Titan Gym. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels (15-5 overall and 10-1 in the Big West) handed Santa Barbara a 77-61 
loss Monday in a game that was never close after the first 10 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton (9-10 and 4-6) lost the first meeting with UNLV this season, 66-63, 
on a desperation 3-pointer by Greg Anthony just before the buzzer. ROBYN 
NORWOOD 
</P>
