</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREGORY GONZALEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cathedral 55, El Segundo 53 -- El Segundo squandered a 16-point second-half 
lead and the Cathedral Phantoms hit two free throws with nine seconds remaining 
to beat the Eagles in front of a frenzied crowd at Cathedral's Brother Bertram 
Gym in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The Eagles finish the regular season 13-10 overall, 9-3 in Santa Fe League 
play. They will finish either tied for second with Cantwell or in third place, 
depending on the outcome of the Cantwell-Cathedral game Friday. Cathedral won 
its second consecutive league title with Wednesday's victory. 
</P>
<P>
El Segundo led, 45-29, with four minutes remaining in the third period but was 
outscored, 26-8, in the last 12 minutes, including 13-6 in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Cathedral's Michael Orozco tied the score at 51 with a layup and then gave the 
Phantoms their first lead of the game at 1:31, 53-51, with another layup. Shawn 
Foster, who led all scorers with 22 points, tied the game with 30 seconds left. 
The Eagles regained possession on a turnover but gave the ball back on a missed 
free throw. Louis Fuentes was fouled with nine seconds to go and made both free 
throws in the one-and-one to give the Phantoms the victory. GREGORY GONZALEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
