<P>
CENTENNIAL COMMITTEE ENDS WITH A SURPLUS OF $54,483 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The committee formed to organize and finance two years of events celebrating 
the 100th birthday of Long Beach ended up in the black. 
</P>
<P>
The International City Celebration reported accumulating a surplus of $54,483 
that will be donated to the city, according to the group's final report. Of 
that, $6,204 was surplus revenue from the sale of tiles and bronze plaques 
mounted in Centennial Plaza in the City Hall complex. 
</P>
<P>
Besides resulting in favorable publicity for the city, the centennial also 
leaves behind some lasting tributes. Ten flag poles and bronze photograph 
display cases were among the improvements made in Centennial Plaza. 
</P>
</TEXT>
