<HEADLINE>
<P>
OCCIDENTAL TO PLAY IN TENNIS EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SAM FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Occidental College women's tennis team leaves for the third annual Las 
Vegas Invitational tournament today. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to Occidental, the tournament field comprises Cal State 
Bakersfield, Utah State, Cal State San Bernardino, UC Riverside and Cal 
Lutheran. The Tigers, who finished third in the Southern California 
Intercollegiate Athletic Conference with a 9-3 record (12-11 overall) last 
season, lost the four top players off that squad to graduation. 
</P>
<P>
Unlike traditional tournaments, the Las Vegas tournament will be contested in 
flights, with each team's top-seeded player meeting the top-seeded players from 
each of the other teams, the No. 2 players meeting the other schools' No. 2 
players and so on. Team scoring is not tabulated under the tournament format. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, Sue Hulse of Occidental won the flight for top-seeded players. SAM 
FARMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
