<HEADLINE>
<P>
POWELL HAS PNEUMONIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JACKSONVILLE, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Retired Supreme Court Justice Lewis F. Powell Jr. has developed pneumonia and 
will remain hospitalized for several more days, a spokeswoman at Baptist 
Medical Center said Wednesday. Powell, 81, is being treated with antibiotics, 
remains in good condition and has no respiratory distress, she said. 
</P>
