SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: EL CAJON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 55-year-old Jamul man suffered fatal head injuries Tuesday night when his 
truck collided with a car at Granite Hills Drive and Madison Avenue in El 
Cajon, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
Robert John Weaklem was driving north on Granite Hills Drive about 9:30 p.m. 
when he failed to stop at Madison Avenue, where there is a stop sign, police 
said. The pickup struck a car eastbound on Madison Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Weaklem was ejected from the truck as it rolled once and crashed through a 
wooden fence behind a house, police said. He was pronounced dead at the scene. 
The car's driver was treated for minor head injuries and released, a police 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was under investigation Wednesday. 
