<HEADLINE>
<P>
BONELLI PARK RULING LAUDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your headline, "Bonelli Park Development Suffers Setback," (Jan. 29), should 
have read, "Local Communities Save Bonelli Park From Commercial 
Overdevelopment," or something similar. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Miriam Vogel's ruling was the right one but 
may yet be only a temporary halt to the county's determination to make its 
parks self-supporting -- like Disneyland. In the 1970s, the entire western 
section of the park was leased indefinitely to a private concessionaire for a 
commercial recreation venture. Regardless of how people may feel about the 
appropriateness of Raging Waters, it is open to the public only three months of 
the year. Thus for nine months of every year this most beautiful section of the 
park is locked off and inaccessible. Do we want more of this? 
</P>
<P>
JERE FRENCH 
</P>
<P>
Claremont 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
