<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ARCADIA; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOL BOARD RACE OPENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents interested in running for the school board in the April 18 election 
are invited to submit declarations of candidacy to the board. 
</P>
<P>
The race will fill two of five board positions. Board member Mary E. Dougherty 
has filed for a second four-year term, but Dr. William Spuck said that because 
of professional commitments, he will not seek reelection. Their terms end June 
30. 
</P>
<P>
Interested people can obtain declaration of candidacy forms at the Arcadia 
Unified School District office or by calling the superintendent's office at 
(818) 446-0131. Completed forms are due on Feb. 22 by 4:30 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
