<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCRIPPS PRESIDENT TO RESIGN IN JUNE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John H. Chandler, president of Scripps College for 13 years, has announced that 
he will resign June 30 to work on research for a book at Oxford University's 
Worcester College. 
</P>
<P>
Howard Brooks, provost at Scripps, will serve as acting president until 
Chandler's successor is chosen. A college spokesman said the board of trustees 
hopes to have the new president by July 1, 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Chandler headed a recently completed campaign that raised about $41 million for 
the women's college, which is one of six in the Claremont Colleges group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
