<P>
PORTLAND SENTENCE FOR GANG MEMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old California gang member has been sentenced to almost four years in 
prison for his role in bringing "crack" cocaine to Portland, Ore., from the Los 
Angeles area. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. District Judge Malcolm Marsh also ordered three years of special 
supervised release following the prison term of Eric Norseweather of Compton. 
</P>
<P>
Norseweather pleaded guilty Dec. 9 to a federal charge of aiding the 
distribution of cocaine in the Portland area from March to August of last year. 
</P>
<P>
Norseweather, who was sentenced Monday, was arrested last June. 
</P>
