<TEXT>
<P>
Syracuse basketball player Derrick Coleman pleaded guilty in Syracuse City 
Court to harassment and disorderly conduct charges stemming from a brawl and 
break-in incident on campus last December. Coleman was sentenced to 50 hours of 
community service and restitution for damages he caused. 
</P>
<P>
Because both of the charges are violations, which are non-criminal offenses, 
Coleman will have no criminal record, his attorney, Donald Martin, said. 
</P>
