<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chicago Board of Trade told its members that it would not stop brokers from 
dual trading -- trading orders for their customers and for themselves at the 
same time -- despite the much publicized federal investigation into alleged 
fraud. However, it said it would assess bigger fines on members who abuse the 
futures markets. The maximum fines assessed by the CBOT against traders will 
soon be increased to $250,000 from $75,000. 
</P>
