<TEXT>
<P>
A trade publication reports that Litton Industries Inc. is interested in buying 
Norden Systems, the United Technologies Corp. division that makes military 
radar systems. A report in the most recent issue of Electronics News said 
Litton, based in Beverly Hills, is looking into buying Norden to improve 
Litton's market position with the military. Officials at UTC, based in 
Hartford, Conn., and Litton declined comment on the report. Norden, which has 
been up for sale since April, has been unprofitable for more than two years. 
</P>
