<P>
Garuda Indonesia Airways, the Indonesian national airline, said it would 
purchase six McDonnell Douglas MD-11 wide-cabin tri-jets at a potential value 
of more than $600 million. The announcement came just one day after five other 
airlines ordered up to 76 of the new jets. "The MD-11s will be able to fly 
