<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PARKS SCORES 28 AS MARINA UPSETS FOUNTAIN VALLEY, 71-68 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Center Cherokee Parks scored 28 points, including a pair of free throws with 22 
seconds remaining, as Marina High School upset Fountain Valley, 71-68, 
Wednesday in a Sunset League boys' basketball game at Marina. 
</P>
<P>
Parks, a 6-foot-10 sophomore, made 11 of 15 shots, had 14 rebounds and blocked 
five shots. Fountain Valley (17-6 overall, 5-4 in league play) had moved to 
within a point, 66-65, with 59 seconds remaining when guard Doug Weaver hit a 
jump shot, but Marina (10-14, 3-6) scored the upset with some accurate free 
throw shooting down the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
In other Sunset League games: 
</P>
<P>
Edison 57, Ocean View 47 -- The host Chargers (13-12, 6-3) outscored Ocean 
View, 18-7, in the fourth quarter to knock the Seahawks out of first place. 
Bryan Murphy scored 15 points and Tom Tyler 13 for Edison. Todd Norman had 18 
points for Ocean View (16-7, 6-3). 
</P>
