<P>
ISRAEL WANTS U.N. OFFICER REMOVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israel today demanded the removal of a Norwegian U.N. commander who compared 
the expulsion of 79 people from Israeli-controlled territory in south Lebanon 
to steps Nazis took in World War II. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Col. J. E. Karlsen, commander of the Norwegian battalion in the U.N. 
Interim Force in Lebanon made the comparison last week in a private meeting 
with Israeli officials. His remark was leaked to the press, and Israel's 
Foreign Ministry complained at the time. However, the ministry now wants him 
removed because he was quoted by a newspaper as saying his comparison succeeded 
in drawing attention to the expulsions, a ministry spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
