<P>
ACTOR FOX WEDDING BRINGS THREATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael J. Fox received 5,000 threatening letters from a woman who was upset he 
got married, a district attorney investigator said today. The woman suspected 
of writing the letters, Tina Marie Ledbetter, 26, was arrested in Westlake 
Village last week but was released after she posted $100,000 bail, investigator 
Gary Schram said. 
</P>
<P>
Fox, 27, who won two Emmys for his portrayal of the insufferable conservative 
son of liberal parents on the NBC series "Family Ties," married his former 
co-star on the show, actress Tracy Pollan, last July. Fox began receiving 
unsigned letters last February, said Al Albergate, spokesman for the Los 
Angeles County District Attorney's office. "The letters threatened the lives of 
Fox, his wife and their yet-to-be-born child," Albergate said. 
</P>
